scopecontent.p:
Contains 12 watercolor drawings by Kyd, a pseudonym for Joseph
                                   Clayton Clarke. Clarke executed a number of watercolor drawings
                                   of "Characters of Dickens." Contains drawings entitled: "Nell";
                                   "Grandfather Trent"; "Quilp"; "Sampson Brass"; "Sally Brass";
                                   "Dick Swiveller"; "The Marchioness"; "Coalin"; "Short"; "Mrs
                                   Jarley"; "Kit"; "Mr Chuckster."

did.unittitle:
Includes a few portraits of Charlotte Brontë; four cabinet
                               photo cards of, and many postcards relating to, the Brontë family;
                               and photos depicting scenes in and around Haworth
